The paper proposes a new algorithm for generating SAT formulas with predefined solutions, which is relevant to the field of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and computational complexity (cs.CC). The algorithm also considers community structures and clause distributions, which are topics related to data structures (cs.DS) and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper presents experimental results and observations, which are relevant to the field of data mining (cs.DM).
